# Audio/Video transcription (requires ffmpeg: brew install ffmpeg)
# v1.20: Moved to Python 3.12+ — dropped openai-whisper
mlx-whisper; sys_platform == "darwin"  # Apple MLX Whisper — fast transcription on Apple Silicon
# Wave 9 — in-process MLX LLM engine (dual-engine, opt-in). mlx-lm / mlx-vlm are installed
# --no-deps in build_backend.sh (like kokoro-mlx) because their DECLARED trees conflict with
# LocalBook's — mlx-vlm pins starlette>=1.0.1 (vs fastapi's <0.51.0) and both pin transformers
# 5.x — yet they RUN fine on the existing transformers 4.57.5 (proven: doc 26 spike + the Wave 9.0
# --no-deps import test: mlx_lm/mlx_vlm/gemma4 all import, and mlx-whisper/kokoro survive). So here
# we pin only their REAL runtime needs:
#   • bump mlx 0.30.6 -> >=0.32 (mlx-lm/mlx-vlm need mlx.core.new_thread_local_stream, absent in
#     0.30.6; mlx-whisper needs only >=0.11 and kokoro is loose, so the bump is verified safe)
#   • sentencepiece + protobuf (gemma / phi tokenizers)
# All lazy-imported — never loaded unless a role's engine == "mlx".
mlx>=0.32; sys_platform == "darwin"        # bumped from 0.30.6 (was transitive via mlx-whisper) for mlx-lm/mlx-vlm
sentencepiece; sys_platform == "darwin"    # mlx-lm/mlx-vlm tokenizers (gemma, phi)
protobuf; sys_platform == "darwin"         # mlx-lm/mlx-vlm tokenizers
# Wave 9.2 — MLX gemma-4 (mlx-vlm/mlx-lm) needs the gemma-4 processor from transformers 5.x
# (4.57.5 raises "Unrecognized processing class"). sentence-transformers 5.2.0 permits it
# (transformers<6.0.0,>=4.41.0); mlx-vlm 0.6.4 caps at <5.13.0. The 5.x cascade forces a
# small consistent subtree bump (huggingface-hub 1.x, click>=8.4.2, safetensors, hf-xet) —
# each verified unconstrained (nothing caps them below). VERIFIED: backend imports,
# sentence-transformers embeds, MLX gemma streams. ⚠️ hf-hub 0→1 has broad HF blast radius
# (TTS/whisper/downloads) — verify in the built app.
transformers>=5.5,<5.13
# Wave 9.6 — torchvision is a HARD requirement for the gemma-4 MLX vision path. transformers 5.x
# `Gemma4Processor` eagerly imports `transformers.models.gemma4.image_processing_gemma4`, whose
# module-level `from torchvision.transforms.v2 import functional` raises ModuleNotFoundError when
# torchvision is absent — surfacing as "Could not import module 'Gemma4Processor'" and forcing an
# Ollama fallback on EVERY gemma MLX call (root cause of the 2026-07-17 fallback storm). mlx-vlm
# replaces the image_processor with its own afterwards, so torchvision is only needed to satisfy
# the import — but the import is unavoidable via AutoProcessor. Pinned to the torch-2.9.1 sibling.
torchvision==0.24.1; sys_platform == "darwin"
